{
  "text": "High CR values indicate a high number of contacts between PUi and PUj; consequently theses PUs are good candidates for merging them into one domain. During the process, a second measure, the average contact probability density (CPD), also used in other method [CITATION_1] , is computed to estimate the quality of newly formed domains.",
